1. This position reports to Operation Manager and understudy the Senior Service &amp; Project Engineer. Jointech Enterprise is committed to an employee-orientated, high performance culture that emphasises empowerment, quality, continuous improvement, and the recruitment and on-going development of a superior workplace.

2. Trainee to be involved in:
a. &nbsp;Daily Attendance to Customer Site for the troubleshooting, Repair and Maintenance of Security System Equipment.&nbsp;
b. &nbsp;Workshop Bench Troubleshooting and Repair of Faulty Equipment
c. &nbsp;To be trained on all new Equipment and System
d. &nbsp;Support New Project Implementation

3. Trainee will acquire the followings:
a. &nbsp;Improve skill level in Electronic &amp; Technical knowledge in actual application.&nbsp;
b. &nbsp;Interpersonal and Communication skill with fellow Colleagues and Customers&nbsp;
c. &nbsp;Understand and Practise Workplace Health and Safety
d. &nbsp;Ability to write Good Service and Technical report

4. Qualification - Polytechnic Diploma

5. Eligibility Criteria for SGUnited:
a. &nbsp;Singapore Citizen or Permanent Residences
b. &nbsp;Graduated or graduating in calendar year 2019 or 2020 from Polytechnics&nbsp;
c. &nbsp;Graduated earlier from Polytechnic and completed National Service in&nbsp;2019 or 2020.